				<title>Re: Intriguing...</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12048201/scp-4597#post-4331782</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 16 Aug 2019 01:24:49 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Weryllium</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2727655</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I had the idea mainly because I <em>also</em> struggle with it myself. To my knowledge we have only one other skip that deals with it in any way (<a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-4414">SCP-4414</a>).</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12048201#post-4325663</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12048201/scp-4597#post-4325663</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 08 Aug 2019 21:41:11 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>cat cherrythorn </wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5556726</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Hmm, so is the living mite thing like a parasite that was causing the regenerative properties, or something?</p> <p>I think i could use a little more information on the guy though. How does he feel about this? Is he okay? What is his history? He seems treated like more of a thing than a person here and I would like to know about him as a person.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12048201#post-4325434</guid>
				<title>Intriguing...</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12048201/scp-4597#post-4325434</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 08 Aug 2019 16:07:13 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>eccodreams</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5104699</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I suffer from dermatillomania myself so I was surprised to see it come up in an SCP considering its public unfamiliarity. Admittedly, it is a shorter article than what's currently being put out there for series 5, but in my opinion that helps it stand out more. Not too descriptive, not too vague. Easy +1 here.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12048201#post-4323985</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12048201/scp-4597#post-4323985</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 06 Aug 2019 21:59:32 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>sachiel187</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5374591</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>gonna hit this with a novote for now. this feels like a series 1 entry, where it gets its creepy weirdness out of the way pretty much immediately. but we're in series 5 and the better entries tend to have more flavor. there's no history, interviews with the subject, or really anything that adds personality to the document. because of that, it's very clinical.</p> <p>that being said, it has potential, and i'm interested to see where this goes. (dermatillomania is something that hits home personally.)</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12048201#post-4323691</guid>
