					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12048201#post-4319676</guid>
				<title>This is great.</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12048201/scp-4597#post-4319676</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 01 Aug 2019 14:56:39 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Qyooo</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5448222</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>A lot of newer skips have a significant amount of length, and I think that this hits the mark of creepy, disgusting, anomalous, and interesting, without being absurdly long. We can read into the psyche of the skip while also understanding how this anomaly can affect their mental state. I love the first sentence, indicating that the researcher is clearly feeling a sense of sympathy for the skip, who must be in SO much pain all the time. Good stuff.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
